## Background
Python FastMCP supports dynamically enabling/disabling tools, resources, and prompts on a per-session basis. This allows servers to adapt available functionality based on user permissions, feature flags, or runtime conditions.

## Requirements

### Session-Level Control
```rust
impl McpContext {
    /// Disable a tool for this session only
    pub fn disable_tool(&self, name: &str) -> Result<(), McpError>

    /// Re-enable a previously disabled tool
    pub fn enable_tool(&self, name: &str) -> Result<(), McpError>

    /// Check if a tool is enabled for this session
    pub fn is_tool_enabled(&self, name: &str) -> bool

    // Same for resources and prompts
    pub fn disable_resource(&self, uri: &str) -> Result<(), McpError>
    pub fn enable_resource(&self, uri: &str) -> Result<(), McpError>
    pub fn disable_prompt(&self, name: &str) -> Result<(), McpError>
    pub fn enable_prompt(&self, name: &str) -> Result<(), McpError>
}
```

### Use Cases
```rust
#[tool]
async fn authenticate(ctx: &McpContext, token: String) -> Result<String, ToolError> {
    let user = validate_token(&token).await?;

    // Enable tools based on user's permissions
    if user.is_admin {
        ctx.enable_tool("admin_panel")?;
        ctx.enable_tool("user_management")?;
    }

    // Disable the auth tool after successful auth
    ctx.disable_tool("authenticate")?;

    Ok(format!("Welcome, {}", user.name))
}
```

### Session State
```rust
struct SessionState {
    disabled_tools: HashSet<String>,
    disabled_resources: HashSet<String>,
    disabled_prompts: HashSet<String>,
}

impl Session {
    fn is_component_enabled(&self, component_type: ComponentType, name: &str) -> bool {
        match component_type {
            ComponentType::Tool => !self.state.disabled_tools.contains(name),
            ComponentType::Resource => !self.state.disabled_resources.contains(name),
            ComponentType::Prompt => !self.state.disabled_prompts.contains(name),
        }
    }
}
```

### List Filtering
```rust
impl Server {
    async fn list_tools(&self, session: &Session) -> ListToolsResult {
        let tools = self.router.list_tools()
            .into_iter()
            .filter(|t| session.is_component_enabled(ComponentType::Tool, &t.name))
            .collect();

        ListToolsResult { tools }
    }
}
```

